        "authorId" : "f7813195-22a2-4200-9f53-7aadb83a2cc9",
        "body" : "No, it is. Our `.d.ts` scope rules are odd - any `export` statement makes it a module, _but_ (separately from that) in a `.d.ts` unless there's an export assignment or export declaration, _every_ top-level declaration is seen at exported, even _without_ an explicit export modifier. AFAIK this was a decision made to reduce the noise in writing declaration files a long time ago.",
